Create an Anaconda Environment.. 
 You only need to create it once like this:
 conda create -n 320_ufo python=3.10 anaconda

Activate the environment:
 conda activate 320_ufo

Navigate to or create a directory for the project
 mkdir name_of_directory

Type the command:
 notepad.exe nuforc_scrape.py
Then copy and paste the python script into the text file and save it

Create your ufo_database by typing
 sqlite3 ufo_database

Create the ufo_sightings table by typing the following at the sqlite> prompt
 CREATE TABLE ufo_sightings ( Characteristics text, Duration text, Location text, Location_Details text, No_Of_Observers text,     Occurred text, Posted text , Reported text, Shape text, comments_and_content text);

Exit out of sqlite3 by pressing ctrl-c

Run nuforc_scrape.py by typing
 python nuforc_scrape.py
